        {
            "_id": "W3v31hVIRNEcLyWS",
            "img": "systems/pf2e/icons/default-icons/action.svg",
            "name": "Starving Invocation",
            "sort": 800000,
            "system": {
                "actionType": {
                    "value": "action"
                },
                "actions": {
                    "value": 2
                },
                "category": "offensive",
                "description": {
                    "value": "<p>The xenia spirit laments the hospitality it was denied, awakening painful hunger in others. Each living creature within 30 feet must attempt a @Check[fortitude|dc:21] save.</p><hr /><p><strong>Critical Success</strong> The creature is immune for 24 hours.</p>\n<p><strong>Success</strong> The creature is unaffected.</p>\n<p><strong>Failure</strong> The creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 1}. A creature sickened in this way can ingest food and drink, and it can only recover from the sickened condition by spending an Interact action to consume food within reach.</p>\n<p><strong>Critical Failure</strong> As failure, but the creature is @UUID[Compendium.pf2e.conditionitems.Item.Sickened]{Sickened 2}.</p>"
                },
